name: D-alanine---D-alanine ligase
comment: Involved with EC 6.3.2.7 (UDP-N-acetylmuramoyl-L-alanyl-D-glutamate---L-lysine ligase) or EC 6.3.2.13 (UDP-N-acetylmuramoyl-L-alanyl-D-glutamate---2,6-diaminopimelate ligase), EC 6.3.2.8 (UDP-N-acetylmuramate---L-alanine ligase), EC 6.3.2.9 (UDP-N-acetylmuramoyl-L-alanine---D-glutamate ligase) and EC 6.3.2.10 (UDP-N-acetylmuramoyl-tripeptide---D-alanyl-D-alanine ligase) in the synthesis of a cell-wall peptide (click here for diagram).

references.title: Enzymatic synthesis of the peptide in bacterial uridine nucleotides. II. Enzymatic synthesis and addition of D-alanyl-D-alanine.
Recent advances in the formation of the bacterial peptidoglycan monomer unit.
